column2: The Asoborn tribe are the ancient ancestors of the Stirlanders in the time of Sigmar.
The Brigundian tribe are the ancient ancestors of the Averlanders in the time of Sigmar and were famed for their riding skills.
The Cherusen tribe are the ancient ancestors of the Hochlanders in the time of Sigmar.
The Endal tribe are the ancient ancestors of the Westerlanders in the time of Sigmar, and builted the foundations of Marienburg and were the first tribe to swear fealty to Sigmar.
The Jutones are the ancient ancestors of the Nordlanders in the time of Sigmar, and were widely renowned for their skills in personal combat.
The Menogoth are the ancient ancestors of the Sollanders in the time of Sigmar.
The Merogen are the ancient ancestors of the Wissenlanders in the time of Sigmar, and are known for being powerful warrior.
The Ostagoths are the ancient ancestors of the Ostermarkers in the time of Sigmar. Who defiantly fought an enormous Orc WAAAGH! until Sigmar's army arrived to turn the tide.
The Taleutens are the ancient ancestors of the Talabeclanders in the time of Sigmar.
Sigmar slew the Teutogen King Artur to win the fealty of the ancient ancestors of the Middenlanders, and Prince Wulcan honored the terms of the duel and served Sigmar loyally.
The Thuringian are the ancient ancestors of the Drakwalders. The Thuringians were feared for their ferocious berserkers.
The Udoses are the ancient ancestors of the Ostlanders in the time of Sigmar. The Udoses were skilled builders who relied on their fortresses to protect them from Norsii raids.
Sigmar hails from the Unberogen tribe, and there descendants still today claim kinship with the Empire's patron god.
The Imperial Pantheon has many gods, perhaps now I should adopt a single patron to worship.

Sigmar -  God of mankind, the founder of The Empire
Taal & Rhya - Gods of agriculture and the wilds
Ulric - God of the winter and primal spheres of war

Manann - God of the sea
Morr - God of death
Verena - Goddess of justice and learning

Myrmidia - Goddess of warfare, strategy, beauty and honour
Shallya - Goddess of mercy and healing
Ranald - God of trickery and thieves
